Step 1: Identify the key numbers.  
• Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -1919526.63  
• Total Current Liabilities (from the balance sheet) = 5637910.70  

Step 2: Calculate the Operating Cash Flow Ratio using the formula:  
  Operating Cash Flow Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities) / (Total Current Liabilities)

Step 3: Substitute in the values:  
  Operating Cash Flow Ratio = -1919526.63 / 5637910.70  
  ≈ -0.3403  

Step 4: Rounding to two decimal places gives -0.34.

Thus, the solution is:

  "solution": {"Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-0.34"}
}
